<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43552663" data-cid="43552663">
    <div id="comment_43552663">
        <header data-points="3" data-reason="Interesting">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Re:Hahahahahahahaha Muahaha"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Re:Hahahahahahahaha Muahaha<span> (3, Interesting)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><span class="author" title="author name and user ID">Anonymous Coward</span> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3687043&cid=43552663">(#43552663)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43552663" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="3" data-reason="Interesting">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>You may not be able to register a<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.ca from outside Canada, but you can register<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.cx outside Christmas Island<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.tv outside Tuvalu<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.bz outside Belize<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.to outside Tonga<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.mx outside Mexico<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.es outside Spain<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.in outside India</p><p>This is not a complete list -- for example, I haven't mentioned that you can register<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.cc outside the Cocos Islands.  I'm just pointing out that you can register some country code TLDs outside that country.  That's probably true of most<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.tv domains and is possible even with larger countries like Mexico, Spain, and India.</p><p>If anything, a<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.amazon domain should be safer than a<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.com domain.  Both<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.co (Columbia) and<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.cm (Cameroon, with presence) are available (and it's possible to get<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.om with an Oman presence), but<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.mazon and<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.amaon seem unlikely.</p></div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_43552663">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="3687043" data-cid="43552663">
                    <button class="btn btn-default call-form" data-sid="43552663" data-pid="43552663" data-cid="43552663"><i class="fa fa-reply"></i> Reply</button>
                    <button class="btn btn-default show-parent" href=""><i class="fa fa-level-up"></i> Parent</button>
