<article class="comment-article com-show" id="tree_43552103" data-cid="43552103">
    <div id="comment_43552103">
        <header data-points="5" data-reason="Insightful">
            <h3 class="comment-title" data-subject="Why have TLDs at all?"><i class="com-toggle fa fa-caret-down"></i>Why have TLDs at all?<span> (5, Insightful)</span></h3>
            <h4 class="avatar-tiny"><a href="//beta.slashdot.org/~Jeff+Fohl" class="author" title="author name and user ID">Jeff Fohl (597433) </a> | about a year ago | <a href="//beta.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=3687043&cid=43552103">(#43552103)</a></h4>
        </header>
        <div id="comment_body_43552103" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="5" data-reason="Insightful">
            <div class="comment-body">Sometimes I wish there were no TLDs at all. They aren't really necessary. They actually make things worse, since any owner of a domain is forced to buy several TLD versions of their domain. They only make sense if you can actually enforce the meaning of the TLD, such as how<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.gov TLDs are enforced.</div>
            <footer class="comment-footer" id="comment_footer_43552103">
                <div class="comment-footer-controls btn-group btn-group-sm" data-sid="3687043" data-cid="43552103">
