        <div id="comment_body_43552593" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="2" data-reason="Normal">
            <div class="comment-body"><p>Sorry to pop your myth but over the past decade I've registered several domains, and so far haven't even had to modify my name a little bit to find an available name. There are plenty of names available - unless you insist on &lt;generic word&gt;.com instead of &lt;your company name&gt;.com - replace<nobr> <wbr></nobr>.com by your own country's tld and you've got even more options.</p><p>Just now I'm building up a new site, planning to register a name for it, and again: no problem. The name that I wanted is available. And this time it's a simple combination of two generic words.</p></div>
